      context: 'Birling\'s philosophy mirrors Adam Smith\'s invisible hand pushed to its selfish extreme. The 1945 audience had just experienced wartime rationing, collective sacrifice, the Blitz, and Beveridge\'s vision of a welfare state. Priestley shows that Birling\'s "look after yourself" philosophy is not just morally wrong but historically discredited \u2014 it produced the very catastrophes Britain had spent six years fighting.',
