      context: 'Sheila represents the younger generation Priestley believed would build the welfare state. Her ability to see Eva as a person, not an economic function, is the foundational moral insight the play demands. Priestley deliberately gives this line to a young woman \u2014 the group with least power in 1912 society has the clearest moral vision.',
