      context: 'The structural symmetry between Stave 1 and Stave 5 is Dickens\' most sophisticated technique. Every negative in Stave 1 has a positive counterpart in Stave 5. "Solitary" \u2192 "merry school-boy." "Tight-fisted" \u2192 "light as a feather." The novella\'s form enacts its content: transformation is structural, not just verbal.',
