      analysis: 'Hyperbole that completes the arc: from "Bah! Humbug!" (worst at Christmas) to the absolute best. "Knowledge" \u2014 Christmas spirit is presented as something learned, not innate. It requires education, which is exactly what the three Ghosts provided. "If any man alive" \u2014 superlative, placing Scrooge above all other human beings in his capacity for Christmas joy. The word "alive" carries extra weight: Marley is dead and cannot change; Scrooge is alive and has. Structurally, "possessed the knowledge" echoes the novella\'s educational structure \u2014 Scrooge was a student, the Ghosts were teachers, and now he has graduated with the highest honours.',
