      analysis: 'Two words that define a character completely. "Bah" \u2014 an explosive consonant expressing contemptuous dismissal, a verbal door-slam. "Humbug" \u2014 fraud, deception, nonsense. Scrooge doesn\'t merely dislike Christmas; he considers it a confidence trick performed on gullible people. The exclamation is aggressive, shutting down conversation before it begins. Structurally, "Bah! Humbug!" is the thesis statement of Scrooge\'s philosophy, and its conspicuous absence in Stave 5 proves the transformation is complete. Dickens creates the novella\'s most famous phrase as a negative marker \u2014 its disappearance is the proof of change. It is the anti-"God bless us, every one" \u2014 rejection versus embrace.',
